				 <tr>
				  <td>
				    <a name="54">&nbsp;</a><br>
				    <div class="NewsHeadline">Echelon Charter</div>
				  </td>
				 </tr>
				 <tr>
				  <td>
				    <div class="NewsInfo">
					GUILD CHARTER -
					Friday, July 06, 2001&nbsp;16:07
					by 
					<a class="NewsLink" href="author_profile.asp?name=Dextor">Dextor</a>
					<br>
				    
				    </div>
				  </td>
				 </tr>
				 <tr>
				   <td>
				     <div class="NewsText" align="justify">
				       What follows is the guild charter. It was approved by Verant overnite on a Saturday, while other guilds were waiting or being told to revise their charters. We can all be proud of that, and need to stick by this document.<br><br>Trevis, level 31 wood-elf bard on the Morrell-Thule proposes to form and lead a guild called “Echelon” for the following reasons and based on the following principals.<br><br>What we stand for:<br>1. Loyalty to our brethren.<br>2. Honor in combat.<br>3. Respect and helpfulness to all deserving citizens of Norrath.<br>4. Strength through unification of diverse classes and races into an organized group.<br><br>Our Main Goals:<br>1. Create a family of heroes that each member can depend on in time of need, helping with quests, etc.<br>2. Make each member as strong, skilled and knowledgeable as possible.<br>3. Exploit all facets of the game including quests, trade skills, and events.<br>4. Advance to the point where we can someday raid the planes, slay the dragons, and become TRUE heroes of Norrath.<br>
				     </div>
				   </td>
				 </tr>		 
				 <tr style="padding-top: 5px">
				   <td>
				     <div class="NewsBar">
				       ( 
				       <!-- <a class="NewsLink" href="news.asp">Back to Newsflash</a> | 
				       <a class="NewsLink" href="mailto:aberube@cazcollege.edu">Email to Author</a> |  -->
				       
				       <a class="NewsLink" href="comment.asp?IDCategory=36&IDNews=54">0 Comments</a> 
				       )
				     </div>
				   </td>
				 </tr>
				</table>
				<br>		      
				
				<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="90%" align="center">
				 <tr>
				  <td>
				    <a name="53">&nbsp;</a><br>
				    <div class="NewsHeadline">Echelon Manifesto</div>
				  </td>
				 </tr>
				 <tr>
				  <td>
				    <div class="NewsInfo">
					GUILD CHARTER -
					Friday, July 06, 2001&nbsp;16:06
					by 
					<a class="NewsLink" href="author_profile.asp?name=Dextor">Dextor</a>
					<br>
				    
				    </div>
				  </td>
				 </tr>
				 <tr>
				   <td>
				     <div class="NewsText" align="justify">
				       This document was written as an addendum to the charter. Unlike the charter, it is flexible, and can be revised or appended at any time. It is NOT absolute guild law, but shud be considered as a reference for decision making.<br><br>These are my thoughts on what a guild shud be like. U don’t hafta agree with them all, but I hope u agree with most of them. If I propose to lead you, you need to know how I feel about these things.<br><br>Formation<br>I don’t wanna form a guild that turns into a bureaucracy of rules and red tape. I’m doin this to help ppl play better. I want us all to keep playing as much as possible, anything that takes away from that is to be avoided. Fancy websites, mandatory guild meetings, weekly newsletters, and such are definitely out.<br>We need to be diverse. We need all races and classes represented. We cannot afford to be one dimensional or weak in any area. I propose a guild leader or officer, for each race and class. All members will be subject to judgement of the leaders of their race and class as well as any senior officer.<br>I will be the leader and plan to be fair, not a tyrant. I hope most of u think im fair and trust my judgement. I reserve the right to have final say but promise not to abuse it. I can and do admit when im wrong.<br><br>Recruiting<br>We should not be overly strict on letting ppl in but we wanna keep out the losers and riff-raff as well. I propose that all members first meet approval of the guild officers of their class and race by fighting with them for at least a half hour. I will then interview the candidate briefly and then the person is accepted or rejected by consensus.<br><br>Twinking<br>I am totally against twinking and want the guild to be against it too. We will help each other camp and quest items but that’s all. We all need to do things ourselves. We will NOT camp items and give them to lowbies that cant survive the camp in groop. Also, we do not want members that play a ton of different characters. We want strong members that want to concentrate on one character to make themselves really powerful. This is to achieve our goal of raiding the planes, slaying the dragons, and becoming TRUE heroes.<br><br>Raids<br>This guild will be doing 2 or 3 raids a week at least. I believe raiding dungeons is far superior to just chasing xp. We wanna hit the dungeons our level so we get xp while doing it tho. This will improve our finances and get members great gear and quest items all at the same time. Members will be REQUIRED to participate in at least one raid a week. We wont be really strict about this, but if u gain a rep as never being there, u will be asked about it. Ppl NEVER participating in raids and quests will be asked to leave the guild.<br><br>Quests<br>Everybody has quests they need help with. All members will be REQUIRED to help any members their level with any quests they need do. Again, not real strict, but anybody gaining a rep as never helping will be asked to leave.<br><br>Decorum<br>I want ppl that will be fair and cordial to all the others in the guild no matter what. We don’t want ppl fighting with other members, being rude, or anything like that. We must all agree to mutually respect each other and play nice. We shud also respect anyone and everyone outside the guild until they give us reason not to. We cant afford to make ourselves look bad by conflicts with other players. We will ignore the bozos. We absolutely despise beggars. We do not give to beggars and no one in the guild is allowed to beg. This is not open to revision or discussion. You can work for your items and money, you can get help with anything, but u must at least do some work for everything.<br><br>Looting<br>One of the main reasons for forming this guild is to get everyone the things they need that they cant get alone. Everybody needs help at sometime. I absolutely HATE rolling for items. Ppl never get what they need like that. When we raid dungeons, or loot high quality items, I want us to agree that those items go to the player with the greatest need. Everybody will get a turn. The items should go to ppl that will wear or use them to increase their power. There is ABSOLUTELY no point or fairness in a warrior looting a mage item, then going out and selling it, when a mage in the groop cud use it to become more powerful, and get other things for the guild down the road.<br>Also ppl who receive help getting items for themselves should immediately participate in a groop to help one of their fellow guilders get something. I hope everyone will understand this and agree, not be blinded by greed.
				     </div>
				   </td>
				 </tr>		 
